== Roasted Sweet Potato ==

Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season
with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{16-18%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Zesty Rice ==

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on
high heat. Add the @jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the
side until ready to serve.

== Lentil Curry ==

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a sieve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Drain the
@king prawns{150%g}.

Once hot, add the @red Thai style paste{50%g}, @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and garlic. Stir-fry until fragrant,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the prawns, @coconut milk{180%ml}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @peanut butter{30%g} and
lentils to the pan. Stir well until combined.

Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: If your peanut butter has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Assembly ==

Once ready, stir the roasted sweet potato, @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and a squeeze
of lime juice into the lentils. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a
little thick.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime
zest.

Share the zesty rice between your #bowls{}. Top with the lentil curry.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!